    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-13T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-13T04:00:00-05:00" n="464"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/406: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bordeaux</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">George</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bordeaux</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-13T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 13, 1937—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 13—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My May 11, 11 a.m. and May 11, 5 p.m. Prefecture at Toulouse informs me prisoners
                    intend when released to proceed to Belgium through frontier at Jeumont and that
                    when notified their American passports will be available only for return to the
                    United States and delivered only on embarkation they persisted in their declared
                    intention, refusing to sign an administrative acknowledgment of this
                    notification.</p>
                <p>French authorities will release party without escort tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
